modules.description: This module defines regular expressions for parsing components of URIs, including IPv4 and IPv6 addresses, URI references, authority sections, and host identifiers. It works directly with string inputs to match and extract these structured components. These patterns are useful for validating and decomposing URIs according to RFC3986 standards in contexts like web servers, clients, or configuration parsers.

This module defines regular expressions for parsing components of URIs, including IPv4 and IPv6 addresses, host names, and authority sections. It directly supports pattern matching and validation of URI elements within string data. Concrete use cases include extracting host information from URLs or validating the structure of network addresses in text.

This module enables precise manipulation and analysis of RFC3986-compliant URIs through operations like component-based modification, percent-encoding, query parameter management, and resolution. It works with structured URI representations (scheme, host, path, query, fragment) and string-based regex validation for parsing addresses or authority sections. Common applications include building or deconstructing URIs in web services, normalizing identifiers for comparison, and extracting structured data from URI components in networked applications.
